title: Australia's Benitec nets $12.8mm in US IPO
text:
Australia's Benitec nets $12.8mm in US IPO Deal Date: Aug-01-2015 / Deal # 201530514 Executive Summary 
Benitec Biopharma Ltd. (gene therapy/silencing), a public Australian company since it IPOd there in 1997, netted $12.8mm in its Nasdaq IPO of 1.5mm ADSs (representing 30mm ordinary shares) for $9.21. The number of ADSs sold was much lower than the 5mm initially planned (at $13.06 each). The company later lowered the terms to 1.9mm ADSs at $10. Investors also received five-year warrants to buy 500k ADSs for $5.50.
